The paper focuses on benchmarking vision-based manipulation tasks on a low-cost robotic platform, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of computer vision techniques for manipulation tasks also suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the implementation and evaluation of deep reinforcement learning, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper emphasizes the reproducibility and scalability of the platform, which suggests a connection to systems and control (cs.SY).
